{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b7ed3a22-0000-4000-8000-000000000003",
    "name": "GiGot — Formidable",
    "description": "Formidable-specific deep-dive collection. Companion to the main GiGot collection.\n\nWhere the main collection is a breadth-first smoke test, this one exercises the semantic details of Formidable-first mode: the §2.7 scaffold matrix (explicit true / explicit false / server-default), structured record merge on disjoint data fields, immutable-meta 409 conflicts, and the /records query DSL (where / sort / limit).\n\nFastest setup:\n1. `./gigot -add-demo-setup` provisions the demo admin. Re-use it — this collection uses its own side-repos (postman-formidable-on/off/default) so it never touches postman-demo.\n2. Start the server.\n3. Import this collection + the `GiGot — local` environment (same one the main collection uses).\n4. Run Collection — folder 01 creates the side-repos, folder 02 issues a token scoped to them, folders 03–05 exercise record behaviors, folder 06 cleans up.\n\nFolder 01 'Scaffold matrix' probes the server-level `formidable_first` flag directly — the 'default' repo's response message reveals whether scaffolding fired. See docs/design/structured-sync-api.md §2.7 for the decision matrix this collection pins down.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{formidableToken}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:3417" },
    { "key": "adminUser", "value": "demo" },
    { "key": "adminPass", "value": "demo-password" },
    { "key": "formidableToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "sideRepoOn", "value": "postman-formidable-on" },
    { "key": "sideRepoOff", "value": "postman-formidable-off" },
    { "key": "sideRepoDefault", "value": "postman-formidable-default" },
    { "key": "serverModeScaffolded", "value": "" },
    { "key": "headVer", "value": "" },
    { "key": "headVer2", "value": "" },
    { "key": "recordB64", "value": "" },
    { "key": "plainRepo", "value": "postman-plain" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 Preamble",
      "description": "Log in as the demo admin so folder 01 can hit admin-gated routes via the session cookie.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{adminUser}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{adminPass}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/login", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["admin", "login"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "01 Scaffold matrix",
      "description": "§2.7 decision matrix probed end-to-end: explicit true / explicit false / unset (server default). Each create is paired with a verify that reads back empty and has_formidable to prove the scaffolding actually happened (or didn't).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create on-repo (scaffold_formidable: true)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{sideRepoOn}}\",\n  \"scaffold_formidable\": true\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "repos"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 or already-exists', () => pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  pm.test('message says scaffolded', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.match(/scaffold/i));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create off-repo (scaffold_formidable: false)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{sideRepoOff}}\",\n  \"scaffold_formidable\": false\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "repos"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 or already-exists', () => pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  pm.test('message does NOT say scaffolded', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().message || '').to.not.match(/scaffold/i);",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create default-repo (flag unset — reveals server mode)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{sideRepoDefault}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "repos"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 or already-exists', () => pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const msg = pm.response.json().message || '';",
                  "  const scaffolded = /scaffold/i.test(msg);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('serverModeScaffolded', scaffolded ? 'true' : 'false');",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('serverModeScaffolded', scaffolded ? 'true' : 'false');",
                  "  pm.test('server mode revealed', () => {",
                  "    console.log('server is running in formidable_first=' + scaffolded);",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 Token",
      "description": "Issue a bearer token scoped to all three side-repos so the record folders downstream can authenticate. Runs after folder 01 so validateRepos accepts the allowlist.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Issue bearer scoped to side-repos (saves {{formidableToken}})",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{adminUser}}\",\n  \"repos\": [\"{{sideRepoOn}}\", \"{{sideRepoOff}}\", \"{{sideRepoDefault}}\", \"{{plainRepo}}\"]\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/tokens", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "admin", "tokens"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('token returned', () => pm.expect(body.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.test('all three side-repos in allowlist', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(body.repos).to.include.members([",
                  "    pm.variables.get('sideRepoOn'),",
                  "    pm.variables.get('sideRepoOff'),",
                  "    pm.variables.get('sideRepoDefault'),",
                  "  ]);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.environment.set('formidableToken', body.token);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('formidableToken', body.token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 Record basics",
      "description": "Put one record into the scaffolded on-repo, then read it back via GET /records. Baseline for the merge + query folders below.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "HEAD of on-repo (saves {{headVer}})",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/head",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "head"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVer', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVer', body.version);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "PUT record rec-1 (Alpha / nl)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"parent_version\": \"{{headVer}}\",\n  \"content_b64\": \"{{recordB64}}\",\n  \"message\": \"postman-formidable: add rec-1\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/files/storage/basic.yaml/rec-1.meta.json",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "files", "storage", "basic.yaml", "rec-1.meta.json"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const rec = {",
                  "  meta: { id: 'rec-1', template: 'basic.yaml',",
                  "          created: '2026-01-01T00:00:00Z', updated: '2026-01-01T00:00:00Z' },",
                  "  data: { name: 'Alpha', country: 'nl' }",
                  "};",
                  "pm.variables.set('recordB64', require('btoa')(JSON.stringify(rec)));"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('version advanced', () => pm.expect(body.version).to.not.eql(pm.variables.get('headVer')));",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVer', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVer', body.version);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "PUT record rec-2 (Beta / uk)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"parent_version\": \"{{headVer}}\",\n  \"content_b64\": \"{{recordB64}}\",\n  \"message\": \"postman-formidable: add rec-2\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/files/storage/basic.yaml/rec-2.meta.json",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "files", "storage", "basic.yaml", "rec-2.meta.json"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const rec = {",
                  "  meta: { id: 'rec-2', template: 'basic.yaml',",
                  "          created: '2026-01-02T00:00:00Z', updated: '2026-01-02T00:00:00Z' },",
                  "  data: { name: 'Beta', country: 'uk' }",
                  "};",
                  "pm.variables.set('recordB64', require('btoa')(JSON.stringify(rec)));"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVer', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVer', body.version);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /records — both rec-1 and rec-2 present",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/records/basic.yaml",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "records", "basic.yaml"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('2 records returned', () => pm.expect(body.records).to.have.lengthOf(2));",
                  "pm.test('records carry both meta + data', () => {",
                  "  body.records.forEach(r => {",
                  "    pm.expect(r).to.have.property('meta');",
                  "    pm.expect(r).to.have.property('data');",
                  "  });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 Merge + conflicts",
      "description": "§10.3 uniform merge rule — two writes to *different* data fields on the same record must merge cleanly. The 'stale parent' write is deliberate: it simulates a client that hadn't pulled between its edit and its save. Immutable meta (created/id/template) is the only path that produces a 409.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "HEAD before the race (saves {{headVer}})",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/head",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "head"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVer', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVer', body.version);",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVer2', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVer2', body.version);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Client A: update rec-1.country → 'uk' (fast-forward)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"parent_version\": \"{{headVer}}\",\n  \"content_b64\": \"{{recordB64}}\",\n  \"message\": \"A: update country\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/files/storage/basic.yaml/rec-1.meta.json",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "files", "storage", "basic.yaml", "rec-1.meta.json"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const rec = {",
                  "  meta: { id: 'rec-1', template: 'basic.yaml',",
                  "          created: '2026-01-01T00:00:00Z', updated: '2026-02-01T00:00:00Z' },",
                  "  data: { name: 'Alpha', country: 'uk' }",
                  "};",
                  "pm.variables.set('recordB64', require('btoa')(JSON.stringify(rec)));"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVer', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVer', body.version);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Client B: update rec-1.name → 'Aleph' with STALE parent (expect merge)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"parent_version\": \"{{headVer2}}\",\n  \"content_b64\": \"{{recordB64}}\",\n  \"message\": \"B: update name (stale parent, different field)\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/files/storage/basic.yaml/rec-1.meta.json",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "files", "storage", "basic.yaml", "rec-1.meta.json"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const rec = {",
                  "  meta: { id: 'rec-1', template: 'basic.yaml',",
                  "          created: '2026-01-01T00:00:00Z', updated: '2026-03-01T00:00:00Z' },",
                  "  data: { name: 'Aleph', country: 'nl' }",
                  "};",
                  "pm.variables.set('recordB64', require('btoa')(JSON.stringify(rec)));"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK (merged, not conflicted)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('version advanced past both client heads', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(body.version).to.not.eql(pm.variables.get('headVer'));",
                  "  pm.expect(body.version).to.not.eql(pm.variables.get('headVer2'));",
                  "});",
                  "pm.environment.set('headVer', body.version);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('headVer', body.version);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify merged state — name=Aleph AND country=uk",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/records/basic.yaml",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "records", "basic.yaml"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const rec1 = pm.response.json().records.find(r => r.meta.id === 'rec-1');",
                  "pm.test('rec-1 found', () => pm.expect(rec1).to.exist);",
                  "pm.test('B\\'s name update landed', () => pm.expect(rec1.data.name).to.eql('Aleph'));",
                  "pm.test('A\\'s country update landed', () => pm.expect(rec1.data.country).to.eql('uk'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Immutable meta.created change → 409 RecordConflict",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"parent_version\": \"{{headVer2}}\",\n  \"content_b64\": \"{{recordB64}}\",\n  \"message\": \"attempt to mutate immutable meta.created\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/files/storage/basic.yaml/rec-1.meta.json",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "files", "storage", "basic.yaml", "rec-1.meta.json"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Change meta.created — server must reject since it's in the",
                  "// immutable set (created / id / template). The immutable-meta",
                  "// guard lives in the merge path, so parent_version must be",
                  "// STALE (we use headVer2, the pre-merge HEAD from step 1) —",
                  "// a fresh-parent write fast-forwards through without the check.",
                  "const rec = {",
                  "  meta: { id: 'rec-1', template: 'basic.yaml',",
                  "          created: '1999-01-01T00:00:00Z', updated: '2026-04-01T00:00:00Z' },",
                  "  data: { name: 'Aleph', country: 'uk' }",
                  "};",
                  "pm.variables.set('recordB64', require('btoa')(JSON.stringify(rec)));"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('409 Conflict', () => pm.response.to.have.status(409));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('field_conflicts array', () => pm.expect(body.field_conflicts).to.be.an('array').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.test('first conflict names created', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(body.field_conflicts[0].key).to.eql('created');",
                  "  pm.expect(body.field_conflicts[0].reason).to.match(/immutable/i);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "05 Record query DSL",
      "description": "§10.8 filter grammar — where=key<op>value (=, !=, >, >=, <, <=); sort=key (prefix - for desc); limit=N. After folder 04, rec-1 is (Aleph / uk) and rec-2 is (Beta / uk).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "where=country=uk → both records",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/records/basic.yaml?where=country=uk",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "records", "basic.yaml"],
              "query": [{ "key": "where", "value": "country=uk" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('2 records match country=uk', () => pm.expect(body.records).to.have.lengthOf(2));",
                  "pm.test('all matched records have country=uk', () => {",
                  "  body.records.forEach(r => pm.expect(r.data.country).to.eql('uk'));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "where=name=Aleph → only rec-1",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/records/basic.yaml?where=name=Aleph",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "records", "basic.yaml"],
              "query": [{ "key": "where", "value": "name=Aleph" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('exactly 1 record', () => pm.expect(body.records).to.have.lengthOf(1));",
                  "pm.test('it\\'s rec-1', () => pm.expect(body.records[0].meta.id).to.eql('rec-1'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "sort=-name → Beta before Aleph (descending)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/records/basic.yaml?sort=-name",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "records", "basic.yaml"],
              "query": [{ "key": "sort", "value": "-name" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const names = pm.response.json().records.map(r => r.data.name);",
                  "pm.test('descending by name', () => pm.expect(names).to.eql(['Beta', 'Aleph']));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "limit=1 → only one record",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/repos/{{sideRepoOn}}/records/basic.yaml?limit=1",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "repos", "{{sideRepoOn}}", "records", "basic.yaml"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "1" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('limit respected', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().records).to.have.lengthOf(1));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "06 Convert to Formidable",
      "description": "Exercises POST /api/admin/repos/{name}/formidable against the plain repo `postman-plain` that -add-demo-setup provisions. On first run the stamp fires (stamped=true); on subsequent runs the repo is already Formidable (stamped=false). Second call is always idempotent regardless — that's the strict assertion.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Convert postman-plain → stamped",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/repos/{{plainRepo}}/formidable",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "admin", "repos", "{{plainRepo}}", "formidable"]
            },
            "description": "Stamps .formidable/context.json on top of HEAD. Session-authed (noauth override) because the endpoint is admin-only. First run: stamped=true. Re-run after teardown leaves the plain repo in its converted state, so a second whole-collection run sees stamped=false here — that's still valid, the repo does carry the marker."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('stamped is boolean', () => pm.expect(body.stamped).to.be.a('boolean'));",
                  "pm.test('repo now carries marker', () => pm.expect(body.repo.has_formidable).to.eql(true));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Re-convert postman-plain → stamped=false (idempotent)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin/repos/{{plainRepo}}/formidable",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "admin", "repos", "{{plainRepo}}", "formidable"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('idempotent: stamped=false', () => pm.expect(body.stamped).to.eql(false));",
                  "pm.test('marker still present', () => pm.expect(body.repo.has_formidable).to.eql(true));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "07 Teardown",
      "description": "Delete the three side-repos and revoke the token so a second run starts from a clean slate. Uses session auth (noauth override) for the repo deletes since ActionManageRepos is session-only. Note: postman-plain is NOT deleted — it's part of the demo-setup footprint, cleaned up by `./gigot -remove-demo-setup`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Delete on-repo",
